<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") -%>
<h1 class="text-center mt-2">Project Details</h1>
<div class="card mb-3 bg-transparent mt-3 mb-5">
  <img src="/images/Chats.png" class="card-img-top rounded shadow w-75 mx-auto" alt="img">
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title text-center"><i class="fas fa-server"></i> CRUD Application with SQL Database</h5>
    <p class="card-text text-center">“Full-Stack Data Management with Unique Identifiers!”</p>
    <p class="card-text text-center">
      This project is a full-fledged CRUD application that connects to an SQL database to perform Create, Read, Update, and Delete operations. Unlike the client-only version, this app demonstrates how to handle persistent data storage, making it a significant step toward full-stack development.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Key Features:</b>
    <ul>
      <li>Create: Add new records to the database with automatically generated UUIDs for unique identification.</li>
      <li>Read: Retrieve and display data dynamically from the SQL database.</li>
      <li> Update: Modify specific entries using UUIDs to ensure accuracy.</li>
      <li>Delete: Remove records securely and reflect changes in real-time.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>What I Learned:</b>
    <ul>
      <li>Structuring SQL queries for different operations.</li>
      <li> Using the UUID npm package to manage unique identifiers reliably.</li>
      <li>Connecting the frontend and backend for seamless data handling.</li>
      <li>Understanding how server-side logic interacts with persistent storage.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>